@ThinkingandTinkering You hold one great quality of my mother, she just cant throw away stuff I as well am a dear friend of many scrape guys, what world sees as scrape I always find something useful in the discarded equipment just like you, so yes the need of buying something is scarce I by using a thrown away DC Moter had made a friend's Air Conditioners compressor work removing the AC Moter which was there inside using batteries It just did a lovely job!! Rob Sir  I have started making Lithium ferrous phosphate battery packs for EV using brand new A grade cells, I wish to have a aluminium casing for the purpose to put the pack in, but there is one resin that's Electrically non conductive but thermally conductive I wish to use it in the aluminium case to vent heat as it would touch the aluminium casing and do it's job, I foresee two good aspects of using the resin
1) Battery becomes water resistant almost proof of terminals are not shorted. But I do tell people to use silicon sealant over terminals to make them water resistant.
2) this resin will provide a good fit in aluminium casing thereby reducing the vibration effect when mounted on vehicle, also it will throw the heat out if the battery is under pressure!!🌹🌹 Please guide me Rob Sir very warm regards and love from India.

